HOMECOMING is excited to reveal its all-star line up of Nigerian and International artists, who will perform live on-stage at HOMECOMING Festival on April 21st, 2019. The Music Show will feature performances from DJ Obi, DRB, Naira Marley, Odunsi, Octavian, Poco Lee, Prettyboy D-O, Rema, Runtown, Santi, Sho Madjozi, Simi, Skepta, Teni The Entertainer, and Wizkid. <img src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Homecoming-Artist-Flyer-–-Post-1-1152x1152.jpg" alt="" width="1152" height="1152" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-904389 lazyload" /> The HOMECOMING live music show is famous for its unique performance format: replacing a traditional ‘headline’ hierarchy with a more democratic ‘back-to-back’ set up, where artists of all types and genres take the stage in a continuous ‘playlist’ of contemporary music from the African continent and further afield. Expect Afrobeats, Afropop, Hip Hop, Grime, Alté, Afrofusion and plenty more. HOMECOMING LIVE MUSIC SHOW
DATE: April 21st, 2019
VENUE: HARBOUR POINT 4 Wilmot Point Rd Victoria Island
TIME: 7PM – 12AM